The paper discusses complexity classes of equivalence problems, which are fundamental topics in computer science. cs.CC (Computational Complexity) is the most likely category as it deals with the classification of computational problems based on their difficulty. cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) are also likely categories as they are closely related to the study of equivalence relations and canonical forms. cs.IT (Information Theory) and cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) are less likely but still possible categories as they may be relevant to the discussion of complete invariants and decidable equivalence relations.
